            {
               "text": "### Images from Ashmolean\n\nThese images are copyright for Ashmolean and allowed to be used according to the license determined by them.\n\nTo visualize all images, use the left and right arrows on the slide below.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgEA\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgEA', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Fragment of the epic <i>Enmerkar and the lord of Aratta</i>. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite0>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Sumerians - The Dynasties of Uruk: In this section, we explore various Mesopotamian epics, including the Epic of Gilgamesh. These remarkable works not only reflect the cultural and religious aspects of Sumerian civilization but also convey beliefs and narratives that continue to resonate to this day (<htcite4>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgHarappaW\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgHarappaW', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Harappa Seal. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite1>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>History: Cradles of civilization (Parte II): We continue our study by exploring the civilizations of Egypt, Indus Valley, and China (<htcite14>)</li><li>Understanding Texts: The Writing System: More than just a tool for daily use, the writing system is a milestone that allows us to divide human history into prehistory and recorded events (<htcite5>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">3 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgS\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgS', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Estatuillas of the Sixth Dynasty. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite2>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Myths and Believes: What is the extent of the impact of the flood? (<htcite6>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">4 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgKL\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgKL', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Sumerian King List. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite3>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Family: Sumerians (<htcite12>)</li><li>Family: Sumerians (<htcite4>)</li><li>Family: Sumerians (<htcite13>)</li><li>History: Cradles of civilization (Part I) (<htcite7>)</li><li>History: Sumerian King List (<htcite8>)</li><li>History: What is time? (<htcite9>)</li><li>Understanding Texts: Fractionating Texts (<htcite10>)</li><li>Understanding Texts: The Writing System (<htcite5>)</li><li>Myths and Believes: Is it possible to live in the sky? Is the Earth flat? (<htcite11>)</li><li>Myths and Believes: What is the extent of the impact of the flood? (<htcite6>)</li></ul></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
